# Treaty of Tarnow of 1377

Peace and prosperity to last for decades to come!

After extensive negotiations, the Halych and Polish nobility have agreed upon a set of conditions, under which a marriage Union of houses of Piast of Halych and Anjou of Poland is to commence!

People across the Kingdom rejoice, as this union is, perhaps, the single most important event of this generation - continuation of Trojden's illustrious reign, this marriage has found the same foundation of legitimacy and stability Daneil's decision to convert to Catholicism once had - definitive peace on the Western Frontiers. For decades have the people nervously watched the sun waining - watching not only for the last rays of light, but also for men, gruesome and dreadful, carrying the name of Christ, but in a language they knew not. But that has not happened, and for the foreseeable future, shall not either.

The text of the treaty, available only to the nobles of the Court of the Halych-Volhynian Kingdom, is as follows:
||1) Princess Eufemia shall marry Prince Charles Anjou, establishing Prince Charles as Prince-Consort of the King of Halych-Volhynia and a future King-Consort when Eufemia succeeds King Trojden;
2) The House of Anjou is to pay for all the wedding expanses;
3) The Kingdom will remian the Orthodox realm, while some degree of freedom will be granted the descendants of the Union, discression to the Rada of the Halych Nobles to decide upon in the future;
4) Polish Crown will recognize the Kingdom of Halych-Volhynia in it's current borders (includes Volhynia ||fyi||), and disavow war against it or it's constituents for the next 40 years.||

